this place was not like the elephant sanctuary which was for elephants who had been hurt by humans and needed rehabilitation before going back to the wild. They were free to roam wherever. These beautiful creatures were in cages and looked miserable and sedated. It was an incredible experience to be this close but also heartbreaking . They all still had their claws and teeth.. but no way to live. Do not recommend.

Also, not pictured, I went snorkeling. (My close friends know I’m obsessed with coral… like I use to watch blue planet 2 episode 3 coral reefs to fall asleep every night.. lol) all the coral is dead and washing up on beaches and the few little ones that were alive were made into tourist attractions. 1000s coming to crowd around the last living corals.… within my years on this planet, we’ve killed over half of the coral. 😭😭Also, ingredients in sunscreen cause coral bleaching, so you can imagine 1000s of tourist jumping on top of these homes of fish drenched in sunscreen is not helping at all. Some standing on top of the coral and trying to touch last ones alive. Hundreds of boats in and out with so much exhaust in the air :( sorry to be a Debby downer on these posts, but we’re doomed.
Happy new year!!!!💜
